Use Java 21 and Spring Boot 3 for backend.
Use React with Vite for frontend.
Use PostgreSQL as the database.
Follow controller-service-repository layered architecture.
Use DTOs for API requests and responses.
Use JWT for authentication.
Use environment variables for secrets.
Do not hardcode database credentials or JWT secrets.
Write beginner-friendly code with clear comments.
Explain design decisions before major changes.
Prefer simple, interview-ready implementation over overengineering.